1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:02,225
Python is really exciting,

2

00:00:02,225  -->  00:00:04,800
because you can do so many important operations

3

00:00:04,800  -->  00:00:07,360
and types of work with this programming language.

4

00:00:07,360  -->  00:00:10,780
At a high level, Python is an object-oriented programming language,

5

00:00:10,780  -->  00:00:13,320
meaning you can work with different types of data.

6

00:00:13,320  -->  00:00:15,575
But what does that actually mean?

7

00:00:15,575  -->  00:00:18,090
When we think about data science, for example,

8

00:00:18,090  -->  00:00:20,250
Python comes with numerous libraries and

9

00:00:20,250  -->  00:00:23,910
packages to help us analyze and visualize datasets.

10

00:00:23,910  -->  00:00:26,510
We'll be doing that in the project for this course.

11

00:00:26,510  -->  00:00:28,310
You'll see that in a little bit later.

12

00:00:28,310  -->  00:00:31,970
This helps us really understand and analyze the world around us,

13

00:00:31,970  -->  00:00:35,230
like predicting weather patterns or understanding global trends.

14

00:00:35,230  -->  00:00:38,030
Additionally, machine learning and

15

00:00:38,030  -->  00:00:41,610
artificial intelligence are two areas that are very exciting,

16

00:00:41,610  -->  00:00:44,330
and Python is uniquely created to work with them.

17

00:00:44,330  -->  00:00:48,470
You can work with AI models to predict and classify information.

18

00:00:48,470  -->  00:00:50,960
Think about autonomous driving cars,

19

00:00:50,960  -->  00:00:54,195
recommendation systems that suggest movies or products,

20

00:00:54,195  -->  00:00:56,500
or personalized social media feeds.

21

00:00:56,500  -->  00:00:59,520
These are all important use cases for AI,

22

00:00:59,520  -->  00:01:02,695
and Python is optimized for this process.

23

00:01:02,695  -->  00:01:05,640
App development is also very hot right now.

24

00:01:05,640  -->  00:01:09,160
There are powerful and popular frameworks like Flask,

25

00:01:09,160  -->  00:01:11,405
Django, and Streamlit.

26

00:01:11,405  -->  00:01:15,400
These frameworks provide great ways to build applications.

27

00:01:15,400  -->  00:01:18,340
For example, you could create a website to display

28

00:01:18,340  -->  00:01:22,260
your favorite recipes or build a tool to manage your personal finances.

29

00:01:22,260  -->  00:01:26,340
Python is also great for creating different types of automated tasks.

30

00:01:26,340  -->  00:01:29,860
For instance, you can set up scripts to back up your photos

31

00:01:29,860  -->  00:01:33,800
every week or send yourself reminders for important events.

32

00:01:33,800  -->  00:01:36,560
There are many great use cases for Python,

33

00:01:36,560  -->  00:01:40,160
and we're going to work on some of those in this course.
